.TH _PRINTF 3 "2024" "1.0" "_printf Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of printf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.sp
.B int _printf(const char *
.I format
.B , ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function produces output according to a
.I format
as described below. This function writes output to
.B stdout
, the standard output stream.
.SS Format String
The format string is a character string containing conversion specifiers. Each conversion specifier is introduced by the
.B %
character and ends with a conversion character.
.SS Conversion Specifiers
.TP
.B c
Character conversion. Prints a single character.
.TP
.B s
String conversion. Prints a null-terminated string.
.TP
.B d, i
Integer conversion. Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B u
Unsigned integer conversion.
.TP
.B o
Octal conversion.
.TP
.B x, X
Hexadecimal conversion (lowercase/uppercase).
.TP
.B b
Binary conversion (custom).
.TP
.B S
String with non-printable characters shown as \\xHH (custom).
.TP
.B p
Pointer address.
.TP
.B r
Reversed string (custom).
.TP
.B R
ROT13 encoded string (custom).
.TP
.B %
Literal % character.
.SS Flags
.TP
.B +
Print sign for positive numbers.
.TP
.B (space)
Print space before positive numbers.
.TP
.B #
Alternate form (0 for octal, 0x for hex).
.TP
.B 0
Zero-pad numbers.
.TP
.B \-
Left-justify output.
.SS Field Width and Precision
An optional decimal digit string may specify minimum field width. An optional precision may be specified with a period followed by a decimal digit string.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed (excluding null byte).
.SH EXAMPLES
_printf("Hello %s\\n", "World");
.br
_printf("Number: %d\\n", 42);
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3)
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Tariq Almutairi and Owen Mousa.
